WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.167 --> 00:00:05.750
[Tom] There's the Big Dipper,
there's Pisces,

00:00:05.833 --> 00:00:07.958
and there is Orion's Belt.

00:00:08.042 --> 00:00:10.625
Why is it that the only constellation
I can ever find

00:00:10.708 --> 00:00:12.542
is Party the Space Bear?

00:00:12.625 --> 00:00:15.750
[♪ funky bass]

00:00:15.833 --> 00:00:17.167
[Ben] Agh!

00:00:17.250 --> 00:00:20.833
-Ben, stop working and admire the sky.
-I don't have time for that!

00:00:20.917 --> 00:00:22.875
I need to perfect my Listen-O-Scope

00:00:22.958 --> 00:00:26.917
so I can make the science world forget
all my recent embarrassments.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:30.000
What embarrassments?
Buddy, your last few ideas were great.

00:00:30.083 --> 00:00:33.542
[Tom] The Half-Body Transporter,
the Food-Molder.

00:00:33.625 --> 00:00:35.917
-[punch, bell]
-The Shadow-That-Can-Fight-You...

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.500
Hm. OK, yeah,
maybe they were embarrassments.

00:00:39.583 --> 00:00:41.500
But that's about to change!

00:00:41.583 --> 00:00:45.833
-Imagine a telescope for your ears!
-[Angela] Oh, neat!

00:00:45.917 --> 00:00:48.083
I think. Is that neat?

00:00:48.167 --> 00:00:51.292
It better be! I can't stay in this slump.

00:00:51.375 --> 00:00:55.083
If this invention is another dud,
I'm quitting science.

00:00:55.167 --> 00:00:56.958
-[all gasp]
-No!

00:00:57.042 --> 00:00:59.500
Come on, space. Bring the noise.

00:00:59.583 --> 00:01:03.000
Let's go! Show me something cool!

00:01:03.083 --> 00:01:06.292
-[beeping]
-Don't make me beg! Ooh.

00:01:08.750 --> 00:01:09.792
[Ben] Ooh!

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:13.708
Fine, I'm begging!

00:01:15.708 --> 00:01:18.292
Leave me alone with my failure.

00:01:20.208 --> 00:01:24.542
That's it, the end of my career.
I am the worst inventor of all time.

00:01:26.667 --> 00:01:28.167
[sniffles]

00:01:28.958 --> 00:01:32.792
I don't want to look at any stars,
not after what they did to Ben!

00:01:34.875 --> 00:01:36.917
[beeping, whirring]

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:40.417
-Hello! Can you hear me?
-[gasps]

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.292
I am contacting you from space...

00:01:43.375 --> 00:01:45.333
outer space!

00:01:45.417 --> 00:01:49.958
Oh! Ha-ha!
I am the best inventor of all time!

00:01:55.167 --> 00:01:56.417
♪ Wa-oah! ♪

00:02:04.833 --> 00:02:07.875
[yawns] Ben, before you quit science,

00:02:07.958 --> 00:02:10.875
I want you to know that I believe
you'll have a good invention again.

00:02:10.958 --> 00:02:12.917
You mean like the Listen-O-Scope?

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.583
No. They'll laugh at you for that one,
but you'll bounce back!

00:02:15.667 --> 00:02:17.917
Laugh, you say? Ha-ha-ha-ha!

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:20.167
-Uh...
-Once they meet Allen,

00:02:20.250 --> 00:02:22.708
they'll be too busy praising my brilliance
to laugh.

00:02:22.792 --> 00:02:25.833
-Then I'll be the one who's laughing!
-Wait, who's Allen?

00:02:25.917 --> 00:02:28.542
Allen is the alien
I befriended last night.

00:02:28.625 --> 00:02:32.042
I bring you greetings
from the planet... space.

00:02:32.125 --> 00:02:34.250
That thing works? That's incredible!

00:02:34.333 --> 00:02:38.500
And we can understand each other because
Allen is using a universal translator.

00:02:38.583 --> 00:02:41.958
Bingo! Otherwise
all you would hear me saying is...

00:02:42.042 --> 00:02:43.958
[gibberish]

00:02:44.042 --> 00:02:45.625
Just chatting with an alien.

00:02:45.708 --> 00:02:48.417
I should bet they will make
a statue of me, you know.

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:51.667
This is the biggest scientific advancement
since the wheel!

00:02:51.750 --> 00:02:55.375
I come from a planet
where all wheels are square.

00:02:55.458 --> 00:02:58.667
I'm sorry I doubted you.
This is amazing, Ben.

00:02:58.750 --> 00:03:02.625
I forgive you, Tom.
If genius were easy, everyone would do it.

00:03:05.083 --> 00:03:07.792
-Ginger!
-Put this alien deflector on!

00:03:07.875 --> 00:03:10.667
Cause we're at Alien Invasion Alert 6!

00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:13.625
You're worried about Ben's alien?
We just kicked it. He's cool.

00:03:13.708 --> 00:03:16.292
Oh, you think he's cool?
Well that changes...

00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:21.083
nothing - because he's obviously evil
and trying to take over the world,

00:03:21.167 --> 00:03:24.667
like in every alien TV show
and movie ever!

00:03:24.750 --> 00:03:28.875
[nervous laugh] Ben wouldn't let that
happen. He's careful with his science.

00:03:28.958 --> 00:03:32.750
Was he "careful" that day
he turned the toilet into a time portal?

00:03:33.542 --> 00:03:35.875
Aagh!

00:03:36.958 --> 00:03:38.167
You got a point there.

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:41.500
I'm so glad I found you, Allen.

00:03:41.583 --> 00:03:45.042
This Listen-O-Scope was my last chance
for scientific redemption.

00:03:45.125 --> 00:03:48.833
Well, you did it, buddy.
Everyone on my planet thinks you're great.

00:03:48.917 --> 00:03:54.000
Everyone? Wow! No one ever agrees
on anything on this planet.

00:03:54.083 --> 00:03:57.333
That's why we could never make
a planetary defense system!

00:03:57.417 --> 00:04:01.542
-Really? That's good to know.
-We could never fight off an invasion.

00:04:01.625 --> 00:04:05.167
Why, I can list at least four ways
to take over this planet!

00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:09.500
-It's a good thing you're friendly.
-Uh... Do you have any more tinfoil?

00:04:10.583 --> 00:04:14.375
Tom, on his planet,
they wear glasses so they can see worse!

00:04:14.458 --> 00:04:16.000
-It's incredible.
-[door slams]

00:04:17.167 --> 00:04:20.458
Ben, we're worried
your science is out of control.

00:04:20.542 --> 00:04:23.292
Don't be too hard on him.
This could have happened to any of us.

00:04:23.375 --> 00:04:26.542
-You're putting the world in danger.
-So let's break this thing!

00:04:26.625 --> 00:04:28.042
I call first smash!

00:04:28.125 --> 00:04:30.333
Stop! You don't know
what you're talking about.

00:04:30.417 --> 00:04:33.500
With this Listen-O-Scope,
I can bring alien technology to Earth.

00:04:33.583 --> 00:04:36.083
Then all the scientists
will have to respect me,

00:04:36.167 --> 00:04:38.375
and the world will be a better place, too.

00:04:38.458 --> 00:04:40.750
Ben has it all figured out.
Who wants a sandwich?

00:04:40.833 --> 00:04:43.958
-Wait, what? Alien technology?
-Aw...

00:04:44.042 --> 00:04:46.125
Allen gave me plans for a machine.

00:04:46.208 --> 00:04:50.417
I don't know what it does,
but he says it will be... explosive.

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:52.625
-Explosive?
-Mind blowing!

00:04:52.708 --> 00:04:55.000
-Mind blowing?
-Earth-shattering!

00:04:55.083 --> 00:04:59.042
-Don't shatter the Earth!
-Every genius deals with naysayers.

00:04:59.125 --> 00:05:01.000
Well, naysay away!

00:05:01.083 --> 00:05:04.458
But when the Science Statue Society
puts up a statue of me,

00:05:04.542 --> 00:05:07.042
I'm not going to let any of you
look at it!

00:05:08.167 --> 00:05:12.500
Don't you see? He's building a machine
to bring in an alien invasion force.

00:05:12.583 --> 00:05:15.333
So what's our plan?
Give him the benefit of the doubt?

00:05:15.417 --> 00:05:17.333
No. We have to stop him.

00:05:17.417 --> 00:05:19.625
[♪ adventure theme]

00:05:19.708 --> 00:05:20.708
Aagh!

00:05:22.083 --> 00:05:23.125
Waah!

00:05:26.417 --> 00:05:27.667
Aagh!

00:05:32.792 --> 00:05:36.792
A local scientist claims to have
an invention that'll change the world.

00:05:36.875 --> 00:05:39.875
-People are skeptical.
-This better be fast.

00:05:39.958 --> 00:05:43.000
Yes, this had better not be
another classic Ben failure.

00:05:43.083 --> 00:05:45.042
-[Xenon gasps]
-[Ben] A-hem!

00:05:45.125 --> 00:05:49.458
Welcome, great thinkers
and simpleminded viewers at home!

00:05:49.542 --> 00:05:53.083
Today, you all witness
the birth of a new era!

00:05:53.167 --> 00:05:58.125
Ben, what do you have to say to every
scientist you respect and look up to?

00:05:58.208 --> 00:06:02.625
I say to them, "Hello, distinguished
peers! It is good to be your equal."

00:06:02.708 --> 00:06:06.792
You are all about to see something from...
beyond the stars!

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.917
Mission control here.
Tom, are you in Ben's invention?

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.458
-You have to find its master brain.
-We're looking.

00:06:16.542 --> 00:06:21.167
When we find that master brain, we're
gonna punch it in its stupid master face.

00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:23.083
I've got the alien costumes,

00:06:23.167 --> 00:06:25.917
in case everything goes wrong
and we have to blend in.

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.917
Ginger, I don't see a master brain.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:31.958
Look harder!
We are at Invasion Alert 7 here!

00:06:32.042 --> 00:06:35.458
Oh, no. That's the first-most maximum
Invasion Alert there is!

00:06:35.542 --> 00:06:38.583
Behold, my interplanetary device!

00:06:41.250 --> 00:06:43.542
[crowd gasps in awe]

00:06:47.292 --> 00:06:51.125
-The alien army is coming!
-Hank, we're almost out of time!

00:06:51.208 --> 00:06:54.125
Flail your arms wildly
and maybe we'll hit something!

00:06:54.208 --> 00:06:58.083
-I'm sorry, Tom. I can't do that.
-Huh?

00:06:58.167 --> 00:07:01.083
This was designed
by an advanced alien mind,

00:07:01.167 --> 00:07:05.917
so that our planet can join our friends
amongst the stars!

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:09.250
-Behold! The device.
-[gasps]

00:07:10.333 --> 00:07:12.542
For my statue, I'd like this pose.

00:07:12.625 --> 00:07:14.708
Or maybe this pose.

00:07:15.792 --> 00:07:18.750
Um... that's a water slide.

00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.833
What? No, it isn't.

00:07:20.917 --> 00:07:24.833
Look at the way the tubes spiral
in a fun-but-also-safe corkscrew,

00:07:24.917 --> 00:07:27.875
and end in a pit that's clearly designed
to be filled with water.

00:07:27.958 --> 00:07:31.792
-That's definitely a water slide.
-No, it can't be!

00:07:31.875 --> 00:07:36.375
Dude, there's a picture of a starfish
wearing sunglasses on it.

00:07:36.458 --> 00:07:40.750
I thought that was a symbol
from an alien language, signifying a star.

00:07:40.833 --> 00:07:43.292
[laughter]

00:07:44.667 --> 00:07:47.708
Noooo!

00:07:48.625 --> 00:07:52.083
-You know Ben's alien?
-I am Ben's alien.

00:07:52.167 --> 00:07:55.042
[gasp] He's a body swapper! I knew it!

00:07:55.125 --> 00:07:57.375
This is all a big misunderstanding.

00:07:57.458 --> 00:08:00.625
-Which is just another word for a lie.
-[Ginger] Tom, Hank!

00:08:00.708 --> 00:08:04.333
-Where are you?
-Hank here is about to explain.

00:08:04.417 --> 00:08:07.042
-Right, Hank?
-Yeah. Funny story.

00:08:07.125 --> 00:08:09.250
Ben needed a science breakthrough,

00:08:09.333 --> 00:08:13.333
so I thought I could give him one
by pretending to be an alien.

00:08:13.417 --> 00:08:17.500
I used all my knowledge of things
aliens say on TV - oh, it was working!

00:08:17.583 --> 00:08:20.917
But then Ben wanted alien technology
and I don't know that stuff,

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:24.208
so I thought, "Well, who doesn't love
a good water slide?"

00:08:24.292 --> 00:08:26.917
And here we are.
Looks like I really blew it, huh?

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:32.958
-Aw, no fair! We never have space war!
-[Tom] Ben's making a fool of himself

00:08:33.042 --> 00:08:36.042
in front of all of the scientists
he wanted to impress.

00:08:36.125 --> 00:08:40.250
I wish Allen was here.
He'd know just what to do. He's so smart.

00:08:40.333 --> 00:08:43.417
That's it! Angela, bring me the suit.

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:46.042
[crowd laughing]

00:08:47.375 --> 00:08:51.375
This could not have gone worse
for pathetic local inventor Ben.

00:08:51.458 --> 00:08:54.542
-He should quit science forever.
-[rumbling]

00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:59.625
-[rumbling, whirring]
-[Ben] Huh?

00:08:59.708 --> 00:09:00.625
[gasp]

00:09:06.250 --> 00:09:09.292
[♪ spacey, dramatic music]

00:09:09.375 --> 00:09:12.583
♪ Ooo-ooo-oooh

00:09:12.667 --> 00:09:15.000
♪ Ooo-ooh! ♪

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.125
Greetings, scientists of Earth.

00:09:21.750 --> 00:09:25.333
I am the all-knowing alien...

00:09:25.417 --> 00:09:26.542
Allen!

00:09:27.625 --> 00:09:31.833
Allen, why did you trick me? Was this all
some kind of terrible space prank?

00:09:31.917 --> 00:09:39.167
No. You built a water slide
because the Earth needs more sliding.

00:09:40.917 --> 00:09:43.792
Earth needs more sliding, huh?

00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:49.292
Yes! You totally didn't
embarrass yourself today.

00:09:49.375 --> 00:09:52.208
This is my message of peace
to you all.

00:09:52.292 --> 00:09:54.292
Slide, people of Earth!

00:09:54.375 --> 00:09:59.083
Slide into your future!

00:09:59.167 --> 00:10:01.708
Obviously, that's the most
ridiculous thing I've ever--

00:10:01.792 --> 00:10:06.292
Now that I look at it, this is the most
mathematically fun slide I've ever seen.

00:10:06.375 --> 00:10:08.792
Uh... Exactly!

00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:10.333
What he said.

00:10:10.417 --> 00:10:12.542
Ben, you've reached out to the stars

00:10:12.625 --> 00:10:15.875
and brought us amusement
that is out of this world!

00:10:15.958 --> 00:10:18.167
You truly are a genius!

00:10:18.250 --> 00:10:21.833
-[cheering]
-Let's water party, everyone!

00:10:21.917 --> 00:10:22.958
Yay!

00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:26.292
Hey, yeah! Pulled it off!

00:10:27.417 --> 00:10:30.375
You have a lot of explaining to do, Allen.

00:10:30.458 --> 00:10:32.875
Hey, you're the one who thought
you could talk to aliens.

00:10:32.958 --> 00:10:35.042
-Woo-hoo!
-Yeah!

00:10:36.625 --> 00:10:38.167
[splash]

